<!doctype html>
<html lang="en">

<head>
  <meta charset="utf-8">
  <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, minimum-scale=1, initial-scale=1, user-scalable=yes">
  <title>Venny</title>

  <style>
    body {
      margin: 0;
      font-family: system-ui, sans-serif;
      font-size: 18px;
      line-height: 1.5;
    }

    article {
      padding: 16px;
      max-width: 700px;
      margin: 0 auto;
    }
  </style>
</head>


<body>
  <article>
    <h1>Venny</h1>
    <p>Venny is a set of components used to show Venn/Euler Diagrams on a web page.</p>
    <p>It is implemented as framework independent custom-elements, and the layout algorithm is based on <a
        href="https://github.com/benfred/venn.js/">venn.js</a>.</p>

    <h2>Let's get started</h2>
    <p>You can import the project in your JavaScript from NPM or just source it directly in your HTML.</p>
    <p></p>

    <div class="codePanel">
      <pre>
      <code>
        <script type="module" src="https://unpkg.com/venny?module"></script>
        <venn-diagram>
          <venn-set name="A" label="Apples"></venn-set>
          <venn-set name="B" label="Oranges"></venn-set>
          <venn-n sets="A B" label="Fruit"></venn-n>
        </venn-diagram>
      </code>
      </pre>
    </div>
  </article>
</body>

</html>